overs Pilar 4.\n- The CHECKPOINT says \"Inspiração para Mural temporal (Pilar 4) e para estruturar cadência de leitura semanal.\"\n- Tzolkin offers 20 named day signs + 13 numbers = 260-day cycle.\n- It has nahual (spirit animal companion) — conceptually similar to Orixás (Pilar 4) and 64 Gene Keys.\n- Calendar Round = 52 years = unique \"era\" measurement\n- 819-day cycle (4 directions) and 9-cycle modular structure\n- The Dreamspell controversy is a HUGE lesson for Akasha: cultural appropriation, marketing vs scholarship, hidden agendas.\n- True Count debate — when you call something \"Mayan\" but it's not, you betray the elders.\n- For Akasha: this is a STRONG cautionary tale about I Ching (Pilar 5) — we need to cite the source tradition (King Wen, Ten Wings, Fuxi) AND modern re-interpreters (Rudd, Wei).\n\nLet me write the report now. 500+ lines minimum. I'll use the same format as chani-app.md.","signature":"1475383993e793890cb41acb55ab2413eb0bf43460e1dc2e4776989e398abcb3"}],"model":"MiniMax-M3","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard"},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"35801049-37f7-42f0-b5d5-b54c2f1d8f85","uuid":"45d6d419-4fa9-4bf2-a953-16889d11fc0c"}
